			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1711562">
									

<p>Voting against. We have a record of not deleting these things.</p>
<p>On further investigation (actually looking at the page), this is only at -7. It's <strong>not eligible</strong> for deletion, regardless. One a side note, I find it a bit silly that we want to keep <a href="http://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/news-update-01">pages</a> for &quot;historical reasons&quot; all the time, but we want to discard an author's page when they run out of SCPs.</p>
<p>There's an established precedent, one established over Malcolm Maclean's Profile, of not deleting author pages anyway. Previously, there was a suggestion to delete author pages that fell below three owned articles, which was also shot down. I see no reason to delete the page of someone who put time into the wiki, even if they've fallen out of favor.</p>

							</div>

